Candle properties

Colour

• The colour is generally displayed as green and red candles.
• Green candles are bullish, closing higher than the open.t
• Red candles are bearish, closing lower than the open.

Body Size

• The body size represents the degree to which the bulls overcome the bers (green candle) or the bears overcome the bulls (red candle).
• A large body shows incresed commitment
• A small body shows reduced commitment.

Range

• The range of the candle is the distance from the high to the low, and represents the volatility of the price during the trading session.
• A wide range shows increased volatility
• A narrow range shows redused volatility

Shadow Loation

• Shadows above the real body show rejection of higher prices(selling).
• Shadows below the real body show rejection of lower prices(buying)

Doji

Description

• BULLISH or BEARISH single candle Reversal Pattern.
• The open is equal to (or almost equal to) the close,resulting in no real body. Indecision in the market - neither the bulls nor bears are in control.
• The Doji can be found at the top or bottom. The Gravestone Doji is usually found at a top reversal. The Dragonfly Doji is usually found at a bottom reversal.

Description

Setup
A trending market - an uptrend for a bearish reversal, or downtrend for a bullish reversal.
Psychology
• A Doji indicates a `tug-of-war` between the bulls and bears in which neither party was dominant. Price mat have been up and driven up and/or down from the open, but was driven back to close equal to (or almost eqaul to) the opening price. This indecision in the market often precedes a change in trend to either a sideways or a reverse direction trend
The Gravestone Doji is more bearish, and therefore more effective at a market top. The Dragonfly Doji is more bullish, and therefore more effective at a market bottom.
Confirmation
The price trades above the doji at a market bottom, or below the doji at a market top.
